channel.title: I think I got it
channel.description:
I discovered the ports for Runescape is 43594-43595. I was wondering if anyone could happen to use these ports with a account and IP address to get into the RS Servers[br][size=1]Posted at: August 28, 2006, 10:07:33 PM[/size][hr]THe file port is also 8010 [br][size=1]Posted at: August 28, 2006, 10:08:19 PM[/size][hr]Some more info PROTOCOL IS TCP DIRECTION IS OUTBOUND REMOTE HOST IS WWW.RUNESCAPE.COM (ALL THE IPs THAT R RESOLVED FOR RUNESCAPE DOMAIN) REMOTE PORT IS HTTP, PROXY 8080, 8010, 43594-43595 LOCAL PORT IS 43594-43595
It seems that the 43594 Port is outgoing while 43595 is Incoming but 8010 could led directly to Jagex databases
